article.headline: San Diego 82, Creighton 70
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Avi Fogel scored a career-high 22 points as San Diego beat Creighton 82-70 on Friday for its fifth straight victory, the school's longest winning streak in four years. Brice Vounang added 14 points and eight rebounds as San Diego (8-5) expanded on a 36-26 halftime lead to beat Creighton for the first time in four meetings. The Toreros have one more victory during the winning streak than they managed all of last season, when they finished 4-26. Nate Funk scored 17 points and Kellen Miliner had 12 for Creighton (9-4), which won all of the previous matchups with San Diego at home. Fogel went 7-of-9 from both the field and free throw line and had five assists. He set his previous scoring high with 13 points against Southern California on Dec. 10. Vounang recorded 12 points in the second half, starting with five straight that helped the Toreros increase their advantage to 44-28 with 16:32 to go. They led by at least nine points the rest of the way. The Blue Jays matched a season high with 19 turnovers, including 13 in the first half. Facing foul trouble in the second half, they were outscored 17-6 from the line. At the outset, the teams traded the lead six times before San Diego pulled away with a 16-7 run for a 32-23 edge with 2:10 before halftime. Fogel scored eight of his 10 first-half points during that span.
